        <h2>The Economic Pillar</h2>
        <p>Economic sustainability can be considered as the continued success of an economy over time or
            the way
            an
            economy operates in a sustainable manner,
            protecting both the social and environmental components as well.</p>
        <p>Like the other pillars, it must be or try to be everlasting, to support itself and grow
            without
            negatively
            impacting the social, and environmental aspects of the community.</p>
        <p>Something that is easier said than done, since there tends to be a huge correlation between
            economic
            growth
            and
            environmental degradation.</p>
        <p>As we grow as a community, so does our wants and needs which causes a major negative impact
            towards
            the
            environment, by eating away at is ecosystems services
            which ironically are our life-support as well.</p>
